+{"id":"frankenpandas-44vd","title":"[HIGH] fp-conformance 8 cascading aggregate tests fail on opaque assert_is_green; need fixture-level surface","description":"Workspace test (rch exec -- cargo test --workspace --all-targets) shows 351 passed / 8 failed in fp-conformance. The 8 failures all panic with terse messages like 'assertion failed: report.is_green()' or 'CI PIPELINE: FAILED (0/1 gates passed)' — the underlying fixture-level mismatches (37 cases per packet_suite_is_green_for_bootstrap_cases) are buried inside the report payload only when {report:?} is included.\n\nAffected tests (all in crates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs):\n- ci_gate_g6_conformance_evaluates (line 29042)\n- ci_pipeline_conformance_only_runs_and_reports (line 29063)\n- differential_suite_produces_structured_drift (line 27256)\n- failure_forensics_report_clean_when_all_pass (line 28519)\n- e2e_suite_runs_full_pipeline (line 28054)\n- grouped_reports_are_partitioned_per_packet (line 23210)\n- packet_suite_is_green_for_bootstrap_cases (line 20547)\n- differential_all_packets_green (line 27457)\n\nFix: replace the bare assert!(report.is_green()) at each site with a structured failure dump that emits per-case (packet_id, case_id, mismatch_class, mismatch) when report.failed > 0. Pattern already used at 20943 in packet_filter_runs_groupby_aggregate_matrix_packet ('expected report green: {report:?}'). Apply the same pattern to all 8 sites. Bonus: write the dump to a JSONL artifact under artifacts/ so the reaper can ingest it.\n\nImpact: turns 8 'opaque cascade' failures into actionable per-case records that downstream agents can pick off without re-running each top-level test.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:35.846664619Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:04:35.846664619Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
